Summary of Material Information:

  • Strategic Review Outcome:
  • Slowed Bankable Feasibility Study (BFS) and approvals process to conserve cash due to low vanadium prices (expected to persist for 2-3 years).

  • Focus shifted to:

    • Metallurgical test work (new concentrate-to-electrolyte pathway).
    • Reserve drilling (2025) for higher-grade inventory.
    • VFB demonstration plant (2026).

  • Capital Preservation:

  • Non-critical expenditure minimized to extend cash runway beyond 2 years.

  • Board/Executive Changes:

  • MD Jon Price and Technical Director Lily Zhao stepping down (effective 30 June 2025), transitioning to advisory roles.
  • Executive Chair Brendon Grylls to lead reduced-cost structure.

  • Board/Executives to receive shares/options in lieu of salaries (details pending shareholder approval).

  • Partnership Termination:

  • Mutual termination of agreement with Thorion Energy (20 June 2025), simplifying capital structure.

  • No capital raising, cash balance, or material financial metrics disclosed.

Material Information Summary (Exploration Results Announcement):

Key Drill Results (Enmore Gold Project – Sunnyside Prospect):

  • 25ENDD006:
  • 107m @ 1.14g/t Au from 189m (incl. 80.5m @ 1.45g/t Au from 193.5m, 35.5m @ 1.94g/t Au from 210.5m, and 9.7m @ 3.18g/t Au from 210.5m).
  • Extends mineralization ~40m SW of prior hole (003), confirming continuity.
  • Visible gold observed in multiple zones (e.g., 212.4–212.7m @ 23.2g/t Au).

Previous Hole Highlights:

  • 25ENDD001: 170m @ 1.75g/t Au (incl. 18.3m @ 9.95g/t Au).
  • 25ENDD002: 172.9m @ 2.07g/t Au (incl. 25m @ 5.23g/t Au).
  • 25ENDD003: 102m @ 1.10g/t Au (incl. 9.7m @ 3.57g/t Au).

Exploration Upside:

  • Mineralization remains open along strike, up-dip, and at depth.
  • Estimated ~75m true width of mineralization parallel to shear zone.

Forward Plans:

  • +10,000m drilling planned (fully funded by current cash balance).
  • Assays pending for holes 007–010 (expected early Q3 2025).

Financial Position:

  • Cash balance: $10.35M (as of 31 March 2025, including $5M May 2025 capital raise).

Market Impact:

  • Results reinforce potential for bulk-tonnage and high-grade gold at Sunnyside.
  • Next catalysts: Additional assay results (Q3) and drilling expansion (August 2025).

Takeover Announcement Summary:

  • Timetable:

  • Scheme Meeting: Q3 2025.

  • Expected Implementation: Q4 2025.

  • Support:

  • Board unanimously recommends (subject to Independent Adviser’s valuation).

  • 13.3% shareholder (Microequities) intends to vote in favor.

Key trading impact: Premium-priced cash exit offer with clear timeline and shareholder support.
